  <entry>
    <title>Recap The TDD Process</title>
    <link href="http://yunminitools.cn/2024/04/15/the-TDD-process/"/>
    <id>http://yunminitools.cn/2024/04/15/the-TDD-process/</id>
    <published>2024-04-15T13:18:07.000Z</published>
    <updated>2024-04-15T13:26:38.261Z</updated>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;From《&lt;strong&gt;Test-Driven Development with Python, 3rd Edition&lt;/strong&gt;》by &lt;strong&gt;Harry Percival&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ve now seen all the main aspects of the TDD process, in practice:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Functional tests&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unit tests&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The unit-test/code cycle&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Refactoring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What does the overall TDD process look like?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We write a test.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We run the test and see it fail.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We write some minimal code to get it a little further.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We rerun the test and repeat until it passes (the unit test / code cycle)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Then, we look for opportunities to refactor our code, using our tests to make sure we don’t break anything.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;And start again from the top!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://cdn.yunminitools.cn/pic/0170-TDD1.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
